{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3440abdc-d353-48ea-9917-414eb6df762c","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since this is a guidance question rather than an existing codebase task, here's how to convert your page:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML root element\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only change** needed is adding `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` (and the `xmlns:vm` namespace). All existing `{Binding ...}` expressions are then compiled against that type.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** for misspelled or missing properties. To make this even stricter, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the XAML compiler warning for binding path issues. Promoting it to an error ensures your build fails on any mismatch (e.g., `{Binding Themee}` → error because `Themee` doesn't exist on `SettingsViewModel`).\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`x:DataType`** can be set on any element, not just the root — useful if a child binds to a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`).\n- To **opt out** for one binding (e.g., a runtime-only binding), use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element or `{Binding Path=Foo, x:DataType=x:Null}`.\n- Compiled bindings also improve performance by skipping reflection at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a4e781e4-21db-4ed3-87ca-fd954ee622c0","outputTokens":665,"requestId":"1439:147A9A:6BA8206:73F2AF7:6A03CC00"},"id":"77683a3c-05e2-43c8-97c9-bf2633456b07","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:55:44.084Z","parentId":"0412813c-30b4-4ab7-a1f8-4c2d608a8a1c"}
